LinkedIn Pinterest HDM Recessed 4 in. Disinfection Module with Care222 Technology By Healthcare Lighting Overview Specifications HDMTM reduces active pathogens* on non-porous surfaces using Ushio Care222 far-UVC disinfection** technology. HDM features a mercury-free far-UVC excimer lamp that contains a patented short pass filter for narrow band 222nm emission. This removes wavelengths that penetrate the living tissue in skin or beyond the tear layer in eyes***. HDM recessed is available in a 4 inch nominal size in a round shape. Available in black, bronze, silver and white finishes. Discreet form factor seamlessly integrates into spaces and is ideal for bathrooms, counter tops and other continual-use areas. UV source emits a soft violet glow from a 1.75" x 2.25" opening when powered. LED status indicator visible from room. UV module serviceable from below. *Refer to product specification sheets at acuitybrands.com/UV-Products for efficacy claims and claim substantiation regarding specific products and pathogens **All references to disinfection are referring generally to the reduction of pathogenic bioburden and are not intended to refer to any specific definition of the term as may be used for other purposes by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration or the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency. Reduction of the pathogenic bioburden is a function of fixture run time and the distance to the UV light source, airflow, room size, shadow areas and/or other factors, and the level of reduction will vary within a specific space. This fixture is not intended for use in the cure, mitigation or prevention of disease and is not certified or approved for use as a medical device by the FDA. It is the obligation of the end-user to consult with a qualified Professional Engineer and a Certified Industrial Hygienist, if applicable, to determine whether this fixture meets the applicable requirements for system performance, code compliance, safety (including safety and hazard alerting signs), suitability and effectiveness for use in a particular application design. *** According to the International Ultraviolet Association Read More Read Less Size 5 IN Light Source UV UV Spectrum 222nm Product Type Downlight Compliance Listing BAA Regulatory Listing UL Voltage Rating 120-277 Mounting Type Recessed Series HDMR Suggested Replacement Products PRODUCT INFORMATION Spec Sheets Document Type Document Title Description Updated View Download Email Spec Sheet HDMR.pdf HDMR Recessed w Care222 Technology 5/2/2024 View Download Email Download Selected Email Selected Need to Create a Submittal Spec Sheet Take Me There Photometry & Revit (BIM) (ies) HDM Recessed .ies (BIM) HDM Recessed BIM Search within... Despite their utilitarian style and simplistic performance, they pose a significant opportunity for an upgrade to LED lighting. The Lithonia Lighting BarnGuard LED security light has it all with its white light, high CRI, instant-on, and low energy consumption. Low-Bay Luminaire By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The VCVL and VCVL Ultimate (VCVLX) LEDs unite visual comfort, optical performance, and energy savings in one visually stunning package you can install anywhere. These luminaires minimize high angle glare and eliminate LED pixilation for maximum comfort. The dedicated up-light option eases contrast between the luminaire and the ceiling, creating a more visually comfortable environment. VCVL and VCVLX offer four distributions and seven lumen packages for the most complete, versatile luminaire package to illuminate the entryways, large open areas, and other common spaces in your lighting site plan. With our array of suspended and ceiling mounting options, you can illuminate any building style or architectural plan. LED Wrap By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The Lithonia Lighting FML4W LED Wraparound provides ambient lighting for surface-mount applications. Perfect for retrofit, its wide body helps cover-up the area where a fixture is being replaced. The FML4W wrap is ideal for both residential and commercial spaces, such as laundry rooms, utility rooms, kitchens, basements, stairwells, hallways, and offices. A lumen switching option, for ALO6 models, allows adjustment from 4000 to 5000 to 6000 lumens.  Triac Dimming(TD): Wrap is 5,000 lumens at 120V only. TD is dimmable through line voltage.  ALO6: Wraps are switchable between 4,000, 5,000 and 6,000 lumens (MVOLT).  ZT: Wraps produce 5,000 lumens (MVOLT). Dimmable through 0-10V. Two ALO Packages  8,000 and 14,000 Lumens or 21,000 and 25,000 Lumens By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications When your project calls for low initial cost and high energy savings, the Lithonia Lighting ESX1 LED area luminaire delivers. ESX1 is ideal for one-for-one replacement of HID area lighting and provides up to 76% energy savings, long service life and fast payback. The ESX1 delivers 8,000 to 25,000 lumens allowing it to replace 150W to 400W HID luminaires. All ESX luminaires feature adjustable light output, providing two light levels from one product, allowing greater flexibility while helping reduce inventory costs. All luminaires feature a reversible arm that allows for mounting on both round and square poles. Three configurations of ESX1 luminaires are stocked in Acuity Brands distribution centers. The ESX1 offers a complete area lighting package and provides the combination of best product value, best price, and best delivery. Login/Register Compare Clear All Home Products ESXF1 LED Floodlight Share Email Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest Compare Share Email Facebook Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest ESXF1 LED Floodlight Adjustable + Switchable + Selectable; Replaces 75W to 150W HID By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The Lithonia Lighting ESXF1 LED floodlight is an all-in-one flood that gives ultimate versatility by offering 36 configurations in one product. Delivering superior illumination and also offers easy access to controls for color switching, lumen switching and selectable photocell. ESXF1 comes with the two most common mountings already included in the box, making on-the-spot reconfiguring quick and easy. No more go-backs! The ESXF family has five sizes with lumen packages ranging from 1,500 to 50,000 lumens and are designed to replace 150W to 500W Quartz or 75W to 1000W HID floodlights. Suitable for both professionals and DIYers, these floodlights offer a wide flood distribution (7x7) and DLC Premium performance, making it a one-stop-shop for all floodlighting needs. Twitter LinkedIn Pinterest JEBL LED High Bay Lithonia Lighting Round LED High Bay By Lithonia Lighting Overview Specifications The JEBL Round LED high bay from Lithonia Lighting is built to outlast the competition. Maintaining exceptional light levels even at high ambient temperatures and able to withstand moisture, dust and airborne contaminants. The JEBL is durable, easy to install, can be used in multiple applications and saves you time and money! It's an even more affordable LED solution for users looking for a better option than the typical throw away high bay while offering an ideal one-for-one replacement of conventional HID and fluorescent high bay systems  JEBL is the one to beat! It is used for both indoor and outdoor applications. Custom-Built LMR-240-UF Cables to your specs  Dispatched within 24 hours. Description Specification Additional information Product Downloads Connectors Hardware & Tools Description LMR-240-UF cable is an Ultra Flexible Low Loss Communications Coaxial cable, supplied in any length  manufactured by Times Microwave Systems and available from McGill Microwave  Authorised Distributor of all Times Microwave products. LMR-240-UF Background LMR-240-UF Coaxial cable is a very popular product within the Times Microwave LMR coaxial cable range. The LMR range is recognised globally as the industry standard ultra low loss, flexible, low cost, lightweight, DC  6GHz coaxial cable solution for many RF applications. This is also backed up by the best warranty and technical support in the business. Why choose LMR-240-UF LMR-240-UF has excellent reliability, unsurpassed flexibility and ultra low attenuation. The LMR-240-UF cable was designed to give more flexibility than the LMR-240 cable. It has loss figures comparable to the extremely rigid corrugated coaxial cables however manages to achieve similar flexibility to that of high loss RG Cables. LMR-240-UF is around 40% lower attenuation than competing RG Air-Dielectric type Cables. How is the LMR-240-UF low loss figures achieved This is achieved due to the cable construction specifications. The centre conductor uses a high conductivity, Bare copper stranded centre conductor. The dielectric is nitrogen injected, foamed, closed cell, Polyethylene which helps achieve 80% Velocity of Propagation. The Dielectric has a Aluminium foil outer conductor, which is chemically bonded on to it. Due to the cable construction, The attenuation is significantly lower as compared to single shielded coaxial cables. Outer Jacket All UltraFlex LMR coaxial cables comes with a TPE outer jacket. This ensures maximum flexibility for repeated or periodic flexures. Frequency Operating Band LMR-240-UF is designed to operate excellent from DC  6GHz. For any frequency band at VHF and above LMR is the obvious choice. Should you find your RF system operates at above 1GHz, LMR is once again, your best option, as RG cable typically isn t compatible with any frequency in excess of 1GHz. Applications LMR-240-UF Ultra Flexible Low Loss Communications Coaxial Cable is ideal for: Jumper Assemblies in Wireless Communications Systems Short Antenna Feeder runs WLL GPS LMR WLAN WISP WiMAX SCADA Radio antennas or receivers TVRO Mobile Antennas High gain 4G antennas Any application that requires additional flexibility Attenuation dB figures per 100m 30 MHz : 5.3dB 50 MHz : 6.8dB 150 MHz : 11.9dB 220 MHz : 14.4dB 450 MHz : 20.8dB 900 MHz : 29.8dB 1500 MHz : 38.9dB 1800 MHz : 42.8dB 2000 MHz: 45.2dB 2500 MHz: 50.9dB 5800 MHz: 80.1dB Temperature range: -400C  +850C Inner Conductor: Stranded BC (1.42mm) Dielectric: Foam PE (3.81mm) Outer conductor: Aluminium tape (3.94mm) Overall Braid: Tinned copper (4.52mm) Jacket: Black TPE (6.10mm) Mechanical Specifications Bend Radius: installation 19.1mm Bend Radius: repeated 63.5mm Bending Moment: 0.34Nm Weight lb/ft 0.05 Kg/M Tensile Strength 36.3Kg Flat Plate Crush: 0.36Kg/mm Connectors At McGill Microwave systems, we supply a huge range of connectors that include all the common interface modes. content: TITINES microwsve svsrens LMR -195-UF UltraFlex Communications Coax Ideal for.   + Jumper Assemblies in Wireless Communications Systems + Short Antenna Feeder runs + Any application that requires additional flexibility + LMR . UltraFlex has a stranded center conductor and rubber outer jacket designed for multiple bending! feexing cycles. It is used for both indoor and outdoor applications.   + Flexibility andbendabiity are hallmarks ofthe LMR- UF cable design. The flexible outer conductor enables the tightest bend radius available for any cable of similar size and performance. + Low Loss is another hallmark feature of LMR- UF Size forsizeLMR has the lowestloss of any flexible cable and comparable loss to semirigid hard-line cables,  RF Shielding is 50 dB greater than typical single shielded coax (40 4B). The muli-ply bonded foil outer conductor is rated conservatively at> 90 dB (i.e.>180 {4B between two adjacent cables). + Weatherability: LMR-UF cables are designed for outdoor exposure and havea life expectancy in excess of 10 years + Connectors: Awide vaiey ofconnectorsare available for LMR cable, including all common interface types, reverse polarity, and solder-on center pins. Most LMR connectors employ crimp outeratachment using standard hex crimp sizes. + Cable Assemblies: All LMR-UF eable types are available a pre-terminated cable assemblies. Cables are both UL and CSA\istes (CMPICATVP),  = LIIR-DB: Watertight cables with an inet Roding Compound injected inthe bra to completly climinate the possibilty of any water migration  with 910 year warranty! In both cases, power can be routed tothe LEDs on a printed cult (pc) board tru the pc board via these Connector families, The Card Edge version allows the matin ofa LED drver pe board perpendicular tothe LED pe board. The horizontal connection between PCBs enables and the mechanism of absorbing the PCB misalignment has been Installed considering the parallel use for the connector. Fork type contact that has a high Contact pressure (receptacle side) and enough mating stroke provide the stable contact performance even if the PCB expands and contracts due to heat.   + Absorption misalignment mechanism (only connector pitch direction) + The PCB layout is in common with plug and receptacle connectors. + Mechanism for preventing wrong insertion + Crimp type socket that is mated with receptacle connector is available. This connector enables direct connection of the converter board and the LED mounting board with a cable. The pin connector for the LED mounting board is available in embossed reel packaging for SMT automated mounting. It allows reflow solder mounting to the LED mounting board to occur at the same time that other LED chips and SMT electrical parts are mounted,  TRE PM DW. Proprietary. content: Reckoete eu) NECTOR S Power System +Specifications / Product Details Serene) +Cable Assemblies   WHAT S INSIDE   NECTOR S POWER SYSTEM The lighting industry is always changing. It is constantly in pursuit of more energy-efficient products with longer life-spans that can be used in different places under different circumstances. TE Connectivity can assist developers, designers and innovators in gaining a head start in this competitive industry. For over 60 years we have worked with lighting industry leaders providing them with strong competitive advantages. Today, with over 500,000 part numbers, we are a leader in passive electronic components. Tomorrow we can apply our expertise to your design and development programs.   Reccoeta ee eu TE Connectivity's NECTOR S POWER SYSTEM is a flexible, fully pluggable, modular wiring connectors and cabling solution to meet the lighting industry's need for a compact easy-to-install interconnect solution. This 7.5mm connector can easily fit in an 8mm opening compared to other connectors that require much larger openings. The Nector  Line connector is ideal for applications where @ power connection and coupling between lamps are needed, Whether it's showing you our value-added solutions or designing a new product; our commitment to advanced engineering and world-class manufacturing delivers innovation to advance your lighting project. Target Markets Electrical Installation + Lighting instalation Applications + Lighting  Residentia itehen and bathroom + Reta: splay, shelves, commercial erigeration + Horticulture: vertial farming + Commercial Office; small spotlighting + Ship and yacht electrical installation Specifications     Euro Style uLsyie + Application 731 4-201 Product 1o8-94018 108-2029 Approvals: DINENIEC60320(V0E) ULI977 Benefits +The smart wiring solution, that can easly fit into smaller 8 mm openings for space saving Improves installation efficiency witha plug and play Interconnection system + Ready-made cable assembles save valuable Installation time and ensure high quality performance throughout the fll ifetime + Reliable and globally approved connector system {GEC and UL certified)  Reccoeta ee eu SEEING IS BELIEVING     Plug-and play principle. It s easy and reliable. Easy, Fast. Compact. It's our job to make connectors easy to use and fast to implement. The compact NECTOR S Line connector allows you to think freely with your design as its flexibility tenables you to move fixtures around product displays for optimum lighting without worrying about any practical implications. Ready-made Cable Assemblies By offering pre-assembled cable systems, TE Connectivity can take away all the hassle in the logistics and manufacturing of these products. Making sure that you can focus en your core competence of designing and delivering lighting equipment. We know the connector system in-and-out and have the right tools to provide you with highly reliable and efficiently produced cable assemblies. The portfolio consists out of the most common standard versions. Additionally, we can offer custom versions tuned to your project needs. (ur connectors ean make your lighting visualizations a reality 540 : ~htonee     Reccoeta ee eu   LIGHTING AS YOU IMAGINED IT   Flexible solutions with every design.  The creative use of light sources Every interior designer knows what proper lighting can do to a room, a desk or a cabinet. It can set a room's ambiance, tone a wall color, or apply an accent on just the right spot. Your wiring can be just as flexible as your imagination   Just give us 2mm If you give us an opening as little as mm, the NECTOR S Line connector can fit t power your lights just about anywhere: in a   ere, You can inet, inside kitchen furniture or in a headboard     The connector is easy to use fast to implement and small enough to fit almost wherever. ws the   tle things The overall atmosphere of any interior lighting design can change because of a 75mm connector. Those few millimeters can give you unparalleled freedom to power your lig Whether itis 250 , 125V or a low voltage, the plug-and-play connector can expand a lighting          Reccoeta ee eu SMALL CONNECTORS, OPTIMAL CONNECTIVITY   Freedom in energy distribution Less use of space, energy, and design equals better lighting installations. With the development of LEDs, lighting fistures are now smaller in size and the possibilities of lighting are expanding. The NECTOR S Line connector can power small fixtures that are   designed to fit into almost any space. Our connector goes places Well balanced lighting inside a refrigerator or freezer system can increase sales. Products are more noticeable, more appealing and consequently they sell better. content: LUMAWISE Endurance S ZHAGA BOOK 18 / Z10 STREET LIGHT CONNECTORS: REDUCE THE COMPLEXITY OF STREET LIGHTING ARCHITECTURE TE Connectivity (TEY's LUMAWISE Endurance S Connector System is a complete set of products specially designed for street and area ighting. There are two main offerings, The original Endurance S Zhaga Book 18 Connector system enables Dai controlled Zhaga Book 18 compliant luminaires while the Endurance S Keyed Connector System enables non-Book I8 applications like ZIO, LUMAWISE Endurance S includes a receptacle, mounted to a street or area light fixture, as well as several base and domes, that together form a robust enclosure for sensor modules and network lighting control systems. The design is compact, UV resistant, P66 seal rated and can be mounted on the top, bottom or even the side of aluminaire, offering flexibility to the designer. Extending fram the Endurance S portfolio isthe S2 receptacle. Offered in bath Zhaga Book 18 and ZIO enabled keyed varieties the S2 receptacle introduces a two-wire per contact solution for ease of wiring and applied cost savings in luminaires with dual node architecture. LUMAWISE ENDURANCE $ CONNECTORS. HAVE BEEN DESIGNED AS A STAND- ALONE SYSTEM AND CAN BE USED IN A. COMPLEMENTARY FUNCTION AS AN AUXILIARY SENSOR MODULE WHEN. ADDITIONAL FUNCTIONALITY IS REQUIRED IN ANSI/NEMA BASED LIGHTING FIXTURES. INSTALLATION IS EASY AND FAST. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California. Rugged Power Supply Design Services Timing & Synchronization Services Microsemi Corporation, a wholly owned subsidiary of Microchip Technology Inc. (Nasdaq: MCHP), offers a comprehensive portfolio of semiconductor and system solutions for communications, defense & security, aerospace and industrial markets. Products include high-performance and radiation-hardened analog mixed-signal integrated circuits, FPGAs, SoCs and ASICs; power management products; timing and synchronization devices and precise time solutions, setting the world's standard for time; voice processing devices; RF solutions; discrete components; enterprise storage and communication solutions, security technologies and scalable anti-tamper products; Ethernet solutions; Power-over-Ethernet ICs and midspans; as well as custom design capabilities and services. Microsemi is headquartered in Aliso Viejo, California.
